<div class="row no-margin z-depth-2 col s12 sticky-navigation" style="padding-top: 10px; padding-bottom: 10px; position: fixed; width: 100%">
  <div class="col s12 valign-wrapper">
    <div class="col s4 m2 no-margin" style="margin: 0px">
      <a href="/users">
        <img src="/images/bluebird-blue-text.png" alt="" class="responsive-img"/>
      </a>
    </div>
    <div class="col hide-on-small-only m8 right-align valign">
      <%
       items = {
         'Learn More' => '/why_bluebird',
         'Sell on BlueBird' => '/apply/step1',
         'Buy on BlueBird' => 'signup/step1',
         'Login' => '/users',
       }
       items.each do |name, url|
         link_class = request.fullpath.start_with?(url) ? 'active-sub-nav' : 'black-text'
      %>
        <a href="<%= url %>" class="<%=link_class%>">
          <div class="nav-category-div" style='display: inline-block'>
            <span class='nav-category bold'><%= name %></span>
          </div>
        </a>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<%= render partial: 'partials/signed_out_nav' %>


<div class="col s12">

  <div id="first-div" class="section">
    <div class="parallax-div col s8">
      <div class="row center-align">
        <img src="/images/bluebird-white-text.png" class="responsive-img"/>
      </div>
      <div class="row white-text center-align">
        <h5 class='bold'>Changing the wholesaler-to-retailer marketplace</h5>
        <div class="col s2 offset-s5">
          <h6 class="how-it-works" style="cursor: pointer"><img src="/images/down-icon.png" class='down-icon responsive-img'/></h6>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row no-margin col s12">
    <div class="how-it-works-div section-white center-align col s12">
      <div class="row">
        <h1 class='bold'>How it Works</h1>
      </div>
      <div class="row col s10 offset-s1 left-align">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col s6">
            <h5 class='bold'>1) Wholesaler Sells a Product</h5>
          </div>
          <div class="col s6">
            <h6>-Decide the duration of the sale (7, 10, 14, or 30 days).</h6>
            <h6>-Sets a sale goal in dollars that they want to meet in that duration.</h6>
            <h6>-Offer a discounted price for the product, which will be given if the sales goal is reached.</h6>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col s6">
            <h5 class='bold'>2) Retailers Make Purchase Orders</h5>
          </div>
          <div class="col s6">
            <h6>-BlueBird retailers place purchase orders on the discounted product.</h6>
            <h6>-As the purchase orders are made, the product gets that much closer to the discounted price.</h6>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col s6">
            <h5 class='bold'>3) The Sale Ends</h5>
          </div>
          <div class="col s6">
            <h6>-Once the product has reached its duration, the sale is closed.</h6>
            <h6>-If the product <span style='text-decoration: underline'>has</span> reached the sales goal, the wholesaler gets paid, retailers receive their discount, and the product is shipped.</h6>
            <h6>-If the product <span style='text-decoration: underline'>doesn't</span> reach the sales goal, the wholesaler decides what to do, but retailers are not obligated to purchase.</h6>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
